name: Eleanor Roosevelt
occupation: Anna Eleanor Roosevelt was many things in  her lifetime. She was a wife, a mother but she was also an American politician, diplomat and activist.She has held the position of the First Lady from March 1933 to April 1945 during her husband President Franklin D. Roosevelt's four terms in office, while serving as United States Delegate to the United Nations General Assembly from 1945 to 1952.
achievements: Eleanor was a leading activist for both the rights of women and African Americans. She was also one of the first First Lady's to ever write a daily newspaper column. She had also oversaw the drafting and passage of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights.While also holding also the position of being one of the most influential people of the twentieth century.
